207 template<typename DataType_, int k_ = 1>
208 class SineTensorStatic
209 {
210 static_assert(k_ > 0, "parameter k_ must be a positive integer");
211
212 public:
214 static DataType_ kpi()
215 {
216 return DataType_(k_) * Math::pi<DataType_>();
217 }
218
220 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
221 {
222 return Math::sin(kpi() * x);
223 }
224
226 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
227 {
228 return Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
229 }
230
232 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
233 {
234 return Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
235 }
236
238 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x)
239 {
240 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x);
241 }
242
244 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
245 {
246 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
247 }
248
250 static DataType_ der_y(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
251 {
252 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y);
253 }
254
256 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
257 {
258 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
259 }
260
262 static DataType_ der_y(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
263 {
264 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
265 }
266
268 static DataType_ der_z(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
269 {
270 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::cos(kpi() * z);
271 }
272
274 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x)
275 {
276 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x);
277 }
278
280 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
281 {
282 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
283 }
284
286 static DataType_ der_yy(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
287 {
288 return der_xx(x, y);
289 }
290
292 static DataType_ der_xy(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
293 {
294 return Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y);
295 }
296
298 static DataType_ der_yx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
299 {
300 return der_xy(x, y);
301 }
302
304 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
305 {
306 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
307 }
308
310 static DataType_ der_yy(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
311 {
312 return der_xx(x, y, z);
313 }
314
316 static DataType_ der_zz(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
317 {
318 return der_xx(x, y, z);
319 }
320
322 static DataType_ der_xy(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
323 {
324 return Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
325 }
326
328 static DataType_ der_yx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
329 {
330 return der_xy(x, y, z);
331 }
332
334 static DataType_ der_xz(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
335 {
336 return Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::cos(kpi() * z);
337 }
338
340 static DataType_ der_zx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
341 {
342 return der_xz(x, y, z);
343 }
344
346 static DataType_ der_yz(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
347 {
348 return Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y) * Math::cos(kpi() * z);
349 }
350
352 static DataType_ der_zy(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)

354 return der_yz(x, y, z);

581 template<typename DataType_>
582 class ExpBubbleScalarStatic
583 {
584 public:
586 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
587 {
588 return (Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) - Math::exp(-DataType_(1))) / (DataType_(1) - Math::exp(-DataType_(1)));
589 }
590
592 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x)
593 {
594 return (DataType_(8)*x - DataType_(4))*Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) / (Math::exp(-DataType_(1)) - DataType_(1));
595 }
596
598 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x)
599 {
600 return (DataType_(64)*x*(DataType_(1)-x)-DataType_(8)) * Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) / (Math::exp(-DataType_(1)) - DataType_(1));
601 }
602 }; // class ExpBubbleScalarStatic<...>

649 return DataType_(4) * (DataType_(1) - DataType_(2) * x);

860 template<typename AnalyticFunctionType1, typename AnalyticFunctionType2>
861 class MinOfTwoFunctions :
862 public Analytic::Function
863 {
864 public:
866 static_assert(AnalyticFunctionType1::domain_dim == AnalyticFunctionType2::domain_dim, "domain dimension mismatch");
867
869 static_assert(std::is_same<typename AnalyticFunctionType1::ImageType, Analytic::Image::Scalar>::value, "invalid image type");
870 static_assert(std::is_same<typename AnalyticFunctionType2::ImageType, Analytic::Image::Scalar>::value, "invalid image type");
871
873 static constexpr int domain_dim = AnalyticFunctionType1::domain_dim;
875 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
876
878 static constexpr bool can_value = (AnalyticFunctionType1::can_value && AnalyticFunctionType2::can_value);
880 static constexpr bool can_grad = (AnalyticFunctionType1::can_grad && AnalyticFunctionType2::can_grad);
882 static constexpr bool can_hess = (AnalyticFunctionType1::can_hess && AnalyticFunctionType2::can_hess);
883
884 public:
886 template<typename EvalTraits_>
887 class Evaluator :
888 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
889 {
890 public:
892 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
894 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
896 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
898 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
900 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
901
902 private:
904 typename AnalyticFunctionType1::template Evaluator<EvalTraits_> _f1_eval;
906 typename AnalyticFunctionType2::template Evaluator<EvalTraits_> _f2_eval;
907
908 const DataType _eps;
909
910 public:
912 explicit Evaluator(const MinOfTwoFunctions& function) :
913 _f1_eval(function._f1),
914 _f2_eval(function._f2),
915 _eps(Math::eps<DataType>())
916 {
917 }
918
919 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
920 {
921 return Math::min(_f1_eval.value(point), _f2_eval.value(point));
922 }
923
924 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point)
925 {
926 ValueType val1 = _f1_eval.value(point);
927 ValueType val2 = _f2_eval.value(point);
928
929 if(Math::abs(val1-val2) < _eps)
930 return GradientType::null();
931 else if(val1 < val2)
932 return _f1_eval.gradient(point);
933 else
934 return _f2_eval.gradient(point);
935 }
936
937 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point)
938 {
939 ValueType val1 = _f1_eval.value(point);
940 ValueType val2 = _f2_eval.value(point);
941
942 if(Math::abs(val1-val2) < _eps)
943 return HessianType::null();
944 else if(val1 < val2)
945 return _f1_eval.hessian(point);
946 else
947 return _f2_eval.hessian(point);
948 }
949 }; // class MinOfTwoFunctions::Evaluator<...>
950
951 private:
953 const AnalyticFunctionType1& _f1;
955 const AnalyticFunctionType2& _f2;
956
957 public:
959 explicit MinOfTwoFunctions(const AnalyticFunctionType1& f1_, const AnalyticFunctionType2& f2_) :
960 _f1(f1_),
961 _f2(f2_)
962 {
963 }
964 }; // class MinOfTwoFunctions

986 template<typename DataType_>
987 class HeavisideStatic
988 {
989 public:
990
992 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
993 {
994 return ( x < DataType_(0) ) ? DataType_(0) : DataType_(1);
995 }
996
998 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
999 {
1000 return eval(x)*eval(y);
1001 }
1002
1004 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
1005 {
1006 return eval(x)*eval(y)*eval(z);
1007 }
1008
1009 }; // class HeavisideStatic<...>

1055 template<typename DataType_>
1056 class HeavisideRegStatic
1057 {
1058 public:
1059
1061 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
1062 {
1063 return ( x < DataType_(0) ) ? DataType_(0) : DataType_(2)*(Math::cosh(x) - DataType_(1));
1064 }
1065
1067 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
1068 {
1069 return eval(x)*eval(y);
1070 }
1071
1073 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
1074 {
1075 return eval(x)*eval(y)*eval(z);

1236 class PolynomialFunction1D :
1237 public Analytic::Function
1238 {

1252 template<typename EvalTraits_>
1253 class Evaluator :
1254 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
1255 {
1256 public:
1257 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
1258 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
1259 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
1260 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
1261 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
1262
1263 private:
1265 std::vector<DataType> _coeff;
1266
1267 public:
1269 explicit Evaluator(const PolynomialFunction1D& function)
1270 {
1271 for(auto it = function._coeff.begin(); it != function._coeff.end(); ++it)
1272 _coeff.push_back(DataType(*it));
1273 }
1274
1275 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
1276 {
1277 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1278 DataType x = point[0];
1279 DataType y = DataType(0);
1280 for(std::size_t k(_coeff.size()); k > std::size_t(0); )
1281 y = x * y + _coeff[--k];
1282
1283 return y;
1284 }
1285
1286 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
1287 {
1288 std::size_t k = _coeff.size();
1289 if(k <= std::size_t(0))
1290 return GradientType::null();
1291
1292 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1293 DataType x = point[0];
1294 DataType y = DataType(0);
1295 for( ; (--k) > std::size_t(0); )
1296 y = x * y + (_coeff[k] * DataType(k));
1297
1298 return GradientType(y);
1299 }
1300
1301 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
1302 {
1303 std::size_t k = _coeff.size();
1304 if(k <= std::size_t(1))
1305 return HessianType::null();
1306
1307 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1308 DataType x = point[0];
1309 DataType y = DataType(0);
1310 for( ; (--k) > std::size_t(1); )
1311 y = x * y + (_coeff[k] * DataType(k*(k-1)));
1312
1313 return HessianType(y);
1314 }
1315 }; // class PolynomialFunction1D::Evaluator
1316
1317 private:
1319 std::vector<DataType_> _coeff;
1320
1321 public:
1323 PolynomialFunction1D() :
1324 _coeff()
1325 {
1326 }
1327
1334 explicit PolynomialFunction1D(std::initializer_list<DataType_> coeff) :
1335 _coeff(coeff)
1336 {
1337 }
1338
1351 Index set_coeff(Index degree, DataType_ coeff)
1352 {
1353 // check degree
1354 if(Index(_coeff.size()) <= degree)
1355 _coeff.resize(std::size_t(degree+1), DataType_(0));
1356
1357 // set coefficient
1358 _coeff.at(std::size_t(degree)) = coeff;
1359
1360 // return degree+1
1361 return Index(_coeff.size());
1362 }
1363 }; // class PolynomialFunction1D

1716 DataType_ _vmax;
1717
1718 public:
1725 ParProfileBase() :
1726 _x0(0.0), _y0(0.0), _x1(0.0), _y1(1.0), _vmax(1.0)
1727 {
1728 }
1729
1742 explicit ParProfileBase(DataType_ x0, DataType_ y0, DataType_ x1, DataType_ y1, DataType_ vmax = DataType_(1.0)) :
1743 _x0(x0), _y0(y0), _x1(x1), _y1(y1), _vmax(vmax)
1744 {
1745 }
1746
1764 bool parse(const String& sbc)
1765 {
1766 auto li = sbc.find_first_of('(');
1767 auto ri = sbc.find_last_of(')');
1768 if((li == sbc.npos) || (ri == sbc.npos))
1769 return false;
1770
1771 std::deque<String> sv = sbc.substr(li+1, ri-li-1).split_by_string(",");
1772 if((sv.size() < std::size_t(2)) || (sv.size() > std::size_t(3)))
1773 return false;
1774
1775 std::deque<String> sv0 = sv[0].trim().split_by_whitespaces();
1776 std::deque<String> sv1 = sv[1].trim().split_by_whitespaces();
1777 if(sv0.size() != std::size_t(2)) return false;
1778 if(sv1.size() != std::size_t(2)) return false;
1779
1780 if(!sv0[0].parse(_x0)) return false;
1781 if(!sv0[1].parse(_y0)) return false;
1782 if(!sv1[0].parse(_x1)) return false;
1783 if(!sv1[1].parse(_y1)) return false;
1784
1785 if((sv.size() == std::size_t(3)) && !sv.back().parse(_vmax))
1786 return false;
1787
1788 return true;
1789 }
1790 }; // class ParProfileBase

1801 class ParProfileScalar :
1802 public ParProfileBase<DataType_>
1803 {
1804 public:
1805 static constexpr int domain_dim = 2;
1806 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
1807 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
1808 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
1809 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
1810
1811 using ParProfileBase<DataType_>::ParProfileBase;
1812
1813 template<typename Traits_>
1814 class Evaluator :
1815 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<Traits_>
1816 {
1817 protected:
1818 typedef typename Traits_::DataType DataType;
1819 typedef typename Traits_::PointType PointType;
1820 typedef typename Traits_::ValueType ValueType;
1821 typedef typename Traits_::GradientType GradientType;
1822 typedef typename Traits_::HessianType HessianType;
1823
1824 PointType _vo, _ve;
1825 DataType _den, _vmax;
1826
1827 public:
1828 explicit Evaluator(const ParProfileScalar& function)
1829 {
1830 _vo[0] = DataType(function._x0);
1831 _vo[1] = DataType(function._y0);
1832 _ve[0] = DataType(function._x1 - function._x0);
1833 _ve[1] = DataType(function._y1 - function._y0);
1834 _den = DataType(1) / Tiny::dot(_ve, _ve);
1835 _vmax = DataType(function._vmax);
1836 }
1837
1838 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
1839 {
1840 // project point onto line segment
1841 const DataType x = Math::clamp(Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den, DataType(0), DataType(1));
1842 // compute function value
1843 return _vmax * DataType(4) * x * (DataType(1) - x);
1844 }
1845
1846 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point)
1847 {
1848 // project point onto line segment
1849 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
1850
1851 // Note: the gradient has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
1852 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
1853 return GradientType::null();
1854
1855 return (_vmax * _den * DataType(4) * (DataType(1) - DataType(2)*x)) * _ve;
1856 }
1857
1858 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point)
1859 {
1860 // project point onto line segment
1861 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
1862
1863 // Note: the hessian has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
1864 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
1865 return HessianType::null();
1866
1867 HessianType hess;
1868 const DataType v = -DataType(8) * _vmax * _den * _den;
1869 hess[0][0] = v * _ve[0] * _ve[0];
1870 hess[0][1] = hess[1][0] = v * _ve[0] * _ve[1];
1871 hess[1][1] = v * _ve[1] * _ve[1];
1872 return hess;
1873 }
1874 };
1875 }; // class ParProfileScalar

1885 template<typename DataType_>
1886 class ParProfileVector :
1887 public ParProfileBase<DataType_>
1888 {
1889 public:
1890 static constexpr int domain_dim = 2;
1891 typedef Analytic::Image::Vector<2> ImageType;
1892 static constexpr bool can_value = true;

1894 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
1895
1896 using ParProfileBase<DataType_>::ParProfileBase;
1897
1898 template<typename Traits_>
1899 class Evaluator :
1900 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<Traits_>
1901 {
1902 protected:
1903 typedef typename Traits_::DataType DataType;
1904 typedef typename Traits_::PointType PointType;
1905 typedef typename Traits_::ValueType ValueType;
1906 typedef typename Traits_::GradientType GradientType;
1907 typedef typename Traits_::HessianType HessianType;
1908
1909 PointType _vo, _ve, _vn;
1910 DataType _den, _vmax;
1911
1912 public:
1913 explicit Evaluator(const ParProfileVector& function)
1914 {
1915 _vo[0] = DataType(function._x0);
1916 _vo[1] = DataType(function._y0);
1917 _ve[0] = DataType(function._x1 - function._x0);
1918 _ve[1] = DataType(function._y1 - function._y0);
1919 _vn[0] = _ve[1];
1920 _vn[1] = -_ve[0];
1921 _vn.normalize();
1922 _den = DataType(1) / Tiny::dot(_ve, _ve);
1923 _vmax = DataType(function._vmax);
1924 }
1925
1926 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
1927 {
1928 // project point onto line segment
1929 const DataType x = Math::clamp(Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den, DataType(0), DataType(1));
1930 // compute function value
1931 const DataType v = _vmax * DataType(4) * x * (DataType(1) - x);
1932 ValueType val;
1933 val[0] = _vn[0] * v;
1934 val[1] = _vn[1] * v;
1935 return val;
1936 }
1937
1938 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point)
1939 {
1940 // project point onto line segment
1941 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
1942
1943 // Note: the gradient has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
1944 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
1945 return GradientType::null();
1946
1947 const DataType v = _vmax * _den * DataType(4) * (DataType(1) - DataType(2)*x);
1948 GradientType grad;
1949 grad(0,0) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[0];
1950 grad(0,1) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[1];
1951 grad(1,0) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[0];
1952 grad(1,1) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[1];
1953 return grad;
1954 }
1955
1956 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point)
1957 {
1958 // project point onto line segment
1959 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
1960
1961 // Note: the hessian has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
1962 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
1963 return HessianType::null();
1964
1965 const DataType v = -DataType(8) * _vmax * _den * _den;
1966 HessianType hess;
1967 hess(0,0,0) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[0] * _ve[0];
1968 hess(0,1,1) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[1] * _ve[1];
1969 hess(0,1,0) = hess(0,0,1) = v * _vn[0] * _ve[0] * _ve[1];
1970 hess(1,1,0) = hess(1,0,1) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[0] * _ve[1];
1971 hess(1,0,0) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[0] * _ve[0];
1972 hess(1,1,1) = v * _vn[1] * _ve[1] * _ve[1];
1973 return hess;
1974 }
1975 };

2902 {
2903 const DataType x = point[0];
2904 const DataType y = point[1];
2905 const DataType z = point[2];

2916 grad[2] = -pi * Math::cub(re) * (x*z*cx*sy*sz + sx*z*y*cy*sz - sx*cz*sy*x*x - sx*cz*sy*y*y);

3421 class Evaluator :
3422 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
3423 {
3424 public:
3426 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
3428 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
3430 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
3432 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
3434 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
3435
3436 private:
3437 const PointType _origin;
3438 const PointType _axis;
3439 const DataType _v_max;
3440 const DataType _radius_s;
3441
3442 public:
3443 explicit Evaluator(const PoiseuillePipeFlow& function) :
3444 _origin(function.origin),
3445 _axis(PointType(function.axis).normalize()),
3446 _v_max(function.v_max),
3447 _radius_s(DataType(1) / Math::sqr(function.radius))
3448 {
3449 }
3450
3451 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
3452 {
3453 // compute ray to project point onto axis
3454 const PointType q = _origin + Tiny::dot(point - _origin, _axis) * _axis - point;
3455 // compute velocity based on distance to axis and in direction of axis
3456 return _v_max * (DataType(1) - q.norm_euclid_sqr()*_radius_s) * _axis;
3457 }
3458
3459 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
3460 {
3461 // compute ray to project point onto axis
3462 const PointType q = _origin + Tiny::dot(point - _origin, _axis) * _axis - point;
3463 // compute gradient
3464 GradientType grad = GradientType::null();
3465 //grad.add_outer_product(_axis, Tiny::dot(_axis, q)*_axis - q, -DataType(2) * _radius_s * _v_max);
3466 grad.set_outer_product(_axis, q);
3467 grad.add_outer_product(_axis, _axis, -Tiny::dot(_axis, q));
3468 return DataType(2) * _radius_s * _v_max * grad;
3469 }
3470
3471 HessianType hessian(const PointType&) const
3472 {
3473 // seriously, getting this mumbo jumbo below right was mostly a lucky guess...
3474 GradientType grad_q = GradientType::null();
3475 grad_q.set_outer_product(_axis, _axis);
3476 grad_q.add_scalar_main_diag(-DataType(1));
3477 GradientType at_x_a;
3478 at_x_a.set_outer_product(_axis, _axis);
3479 HessianType hess = HessianType::null();
3480 hess.add_vec_mat_outer_product(_axis, grad_q);
3481 hess.add_vec_mat_outer_product(_axis * grad_q, at_x_a, -DataType(1));
3482 return DataType(2) * _radius_s * _v_max * hess;
3483 }

3675 template<typename EvalTraits_>
3676 class Evaluator :
3677 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
3678 {
3679 public:
3681 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
3683 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
3685 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
3687 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
3689 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
3690
3691 private:
3693 const DataType _pi2;
3694
3695 public:
3696 explicit Evaluator(const SineRingVortexVelo2D&) :
3697 _pi2(DataType(2) * Math::pi<DataType>())
3698 {
3699 }
3700
3701 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
3702 {
3703 ValueType val = ValueType::null();
3704 const DataType d = point.norm_euclid();
3705 if(d < DataType(1E-3))
3706 return val;
3707
3708 const DataType s2pdi = Math::sin(_pi2 * d) / d;
3709
3710 val[0] = point[1]*s2pdi;
3711 val[1] = -point[0]*s2pdi;
3712 return val;
3713 }
3714
3715 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
3716 {
3717 GradientType grad = GradientType::null();
3718 const DataType d = point.norm_euclid();
3719 if(d < DataType(1E-3))
3720 return grad;
3721
3722 const DataType x(point[0]), y(point[1]);
3723 const DataType di2 = DataType(1) / (d*d);
3724 const DataType s2pdi = Math::sin(_pi2 * d) / d;
3725 const DataType c2pdi2 = Math::cos(_pi2 * d) * di2;
3726
3727 grad[0][0] = -y*x*s2pdi*di2 + _pi2*y*x*c2pdi2;
3728 grad[0][1] = -y*y*s2pdi*di2 + _pi2*y*y*c2pdi2 + s2pdi;
3729 grad[1][0] = x*x*s2pdi*di2 - _pi2*x*x*c2pdi2 - s2pdi;
3730 grad[1][1] = x*y*s2pdi*di2 - _pi2*y*x*c2pdi2;
3731 return grad;
3732 }
3733
3734 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
3735 {
3736 HessianType hess = HessianType::null();
3737 const DataType d = point.norm_euclid();
3738 if(d < DataType(1E-3))
3739 return hess;
3740
3741 const DataType x(point[0]), y(point[1]);
3742 const DataType di2 = DataType(1) / (d*d);
3743 const DataType s2pdi3 = Math::sin(_pi2 * d) * di2 / d;
3744 const DataType c2pdi2 = Math::cos(_pi2 * d) * di2;
3745 const DataType t3 = DataType(3);
3746
3747 hess[0][0][0] = t3*y*x*x*s2pdi3*di2 - t3*_pi2*y*x*x*c2pdi2*di2 - y*s2pdi3 + _pi2*y*c2pdi2 - _pi2*_pi2*y*x*x*s2pdi3;
3748 hess[0][0][1] =
3749 hess[0][1][0] = t3*y*y*x*s2pdi3*di2 - x*s2pdi3 - t3*_pi2*y*y*x*c2pdi2*di2 + _pi2*x*c2pdi2 - _pi2*_pi2*y*y*x*s2pdi3;
3750 hess[0][1][1] = t3*y*y*y*s2pdi3*di2 - t3*y*s2pdi3 - t3*_pi2*y*y*y*c2pdi2*di2 + t3*_pi2*y*c2pdi2 - _pi2*_pi2*y*y*y*s2pdi3;
3751 hess[1][0][0] = -t3*x*x*x*s2pdi3*di2 + t3*x*s2pdi3 + t3*_pi2*x*x*x*c2pdi2*di2 - t3*_pi2*x*c2pdi2 + _pi2*_pi2*x*x*x*s2pdi3;
3752 hess[1][0][1] =
3753 hess[1][1][0] = -t3*y*x*x*s2pdi3*di2 + t3*_pi2*y*x*x*c2pdi2*di2 + y*s2pdi3 - _pi2*y*c2pdi2 + _pi2*_pi2*y*x*x*s2pdi3;
3754 hess[1][1][1] = -t3*y*y*x*s2pdi3*di2 + x*s2pdi3 + t3*_pi2*y*y*x*c2pdi2*di2 - _pi2*x*c2pdi2 + _pi2*_pi2*y*y*x*s2pdi3;
3755 return hess;
3756 }

4067 template<typename DT_>
4068 class CornerSingularity2D :
4069 public Analytic::Function
4070 {
4071 public:
4072 typedef DT_ DataType;
4073 static constexpr int domain_dim = 2;
4074 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
4075 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
4076 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
4077 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
4078
4079 private:
4080 Tiny::Vector<DataType, 2> base_point;
4081 DataType alpha, k, offset;
4082
4083 public:
4084 CornerSingularity2D() = delete;
4085
4086 CornerSingularity2D(const Tiny::Vector<DT_, 2>& center, Tiny::Vector<DT_, 2> v_1, Tiny::Vector<DT_, 2> v_2, DT_ alpha_ = DT_(1.)) :
4087 base_point(center),
4088 alpha(alpha_)
4089 {
4090 ASSERTM((v_1.norm_euclid_sqr() > Math::eps<DataType>()) && (v_2.norm_euclid_sqr() > Math::eps<DataType>()), "Spanvectors are zero length");
4091 k = Math::pi<DataType>() / Tiny::calculate_opening_angle(v_1,v_2);
4092 offset = Tiny::calculate_opening_angle(Tiny::Vector<DT_, 2>{DataType(1.0), DataType(0.)}, v_1);
4093 }
4094
4095 template<typename Traits_>
4096 class Evaluator :
4097 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<Traits_>
4098 {
4099 public:
4100 typedef typename Traits_::DataType DataType;
4101 typedef typename Traits_::PointType PointType;
4102 typedef typename Traits_::ValueType ValueType;
4103 typedef typename Traits_::GradientType GradientType;
4104 typedef typename Traits_::HessianType HessianType;
4105
4106
4107 Tiny::Vector<DataType, 2> base_point;
4108 const DataType alpha, k, offset;
4109 const DataType eps;
4110
4111 explicit Evaluator(const CornerSingularity2D& func) :
4112 base_point(func.base_point),
4113 alpha(func.alpha),
4114 k(func.k),
4115 offset(func.offset),
4116 eps(Math::eps<DataType>())
4117 {
4118 }
4119
4120 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
4121 {
4122 //first calculate radius
4123 const DataType x = point[0] - base_point[0];
4124 const DataType y = point[1] - base_point[1];
4125 const DataType r = Math::sqrt(Math::sqr(x) + Math::sqr(y));
4126 //TODO: Set x_rel to zero if r is very small?? <- Better conditioning?
4127 const DataType x_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? x/r : DataType(0);
4128 DataType phi = Math::acos(x_rel);
4129 phi = (y >= 0) ? phi : DataType(2)*Math::pi<DataType>()-phi;
4130 return alpha * Math::pow(r, k) * Math::sin(k * (phi - offset));
4131 }
4132
4133 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
4134 {
4135 const DataType x = point[0] - base_point[0];
4136 const DataType y = point[1] - base_point[1];
4137 const DataType r = Math::sqrt(Math::sqr(x) + Math::sqr(y));
4138 const DataType x_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? x/r : DataType(0);
4139 const DataType y_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? y/r : DataType(0);
4140 //Note: While in practice we use a rotated coordinate system to express our polar-coordinate
4141 //based function, we have to use the "real" cos(phi) and sin(phi) values
4142 //for our base transformation, which are conveniently x_rel and y_rel
4143 //TODO: This could be badly conditioned for r -> 0, have to test this...
4144 DataType phi = Math::acos(x_rel);
4145 phi = (y >= 0) ? phi : DataType(2)*Math::pi<DataType>()-phi;
4146 const DataType ex = k * Math::pow(r, k-1);
4147 const DataType sval = Math::sin(k * (phi - offset));
4148 const DataType cval = Math::cos(k * (phi - offset));
4149 GradientType grad;
4150 grad[0] = alpha * ex * (x_rel * sval - y_rel * cval);
4151 grad[1] = alpha * ex * (y_rel * sval + x_rel * cval);
4152 return grad;
4153 }
4154
4155 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
4156 {
4157 const DataType x = point[0] - base_point[0];
4158 const DataType y = point[1] - base_point[1];
4159 const DataType r = Math::sqrt(Math::sqr(x) + Math::sqr(y));
4160 const DataType x_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? x/r : DataType(0);
4161 const DataType y_rel = r > DataType(10.)* eps ? y/r : DataType(0);
4162 DataType phi = Math::acos(x_rel);
4163 phi = (y >= 0) ? phi : DataType(2)*Math::pi<DataType>()-phi;
4164 const DataType ex = k * (k - DataType(1)) * Math::pow(r, k-2);
4165 const DataType sval = Math::sin(k * (phi - offset));
4166 const DataType cval = Math::cos(k * (phi - offset));
4167 HessianType hess;
4168 hess[0][0] = alpha * ex * ((Math::sqr(x_rel) - Math::sqr(y_rel)) * sval - DataType(2) * x_rel * y_rel * cval);
4169 hess[1][1] = -hess[0][0];
4170 hess[0][1] = hess[1][0] = alpha * ex * (DataType(2) * y_rel * x_rel * sval + (Math::sqr(x_rel) - Math::sqr(y_rel)) * cval);

4516 template<int dim_, typename DataType_>
4517 class HarmonicShellFunction :
4518 public Analytic::Function
4519 {
4520 public:
4521 static_assert((1 <= dim_) && (dim_ <= 3), "harmonic shell function is only implemented in 1D, 2D and 3D");
4522
4523 static constexpr int domain_dim = dim_;
4524 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
4525 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
4526 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
4527 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
4528
4529 typedef Tiny::Vector<DataType_, dim_> PointType;
4530
4532 template<typename EvalTraits_>
4533 class Evaluator :
4534 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
4535 {
4536 public:
4538 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
4540 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
4542 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
4544 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
4546 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
4547
4548 private:
4550 const PointType _origin;
4551 const DataType _eps;
4552 const DataType _ln2; // = ln(2)
4553 const DataType _i2ln2; // = 1 /(2*ln(2))
4554
4555 public:
4557 explicit Evaluator(const HarmonicShellFunction& function) :
4558 _origin(function._origin),
4559 _eps(Math::eps<DataType>()),
4560 _ln2(Math::log(DataType(2))),
4561 _i2ln2(DataType(0.5)/_ln2)
4562 {
4563 }
4564
4565 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
4566 {
4567 if constexpr (dim_ == 1)
4568 return DataType(3) - DataType(2) * Math::abs(point[0] - _origin[0]);
4569 else if constexpr(dim_ == 2)
4570 return DataType(1) - _i2ln2 * Math::log((point - _origin).norm_euclid_sqr());
4571 else if constexpr(dim_ == 3)
4572 return DataType(1) / (point - _origin).norm_euclid();
4573 else
4574 return DataType(0);
4575 }
4576
4577 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
4578 {
4579 const DataType norm_sqr = (point - _origin).norm_euclid_sqr();
4580 if(norm_sqr < _eps)
4581 return GradientType::null();
4582
4583 GradientType grad(DataType(0));
4584 if constexpr (dim_ == 1)
4585 grad[0] = DataType(-2) * Math::signum(point[0] - _origin[0]);
4586 else if constexpr(dim_ == 2)
4587 grad = (DataType(-1) / (_ln2 * norm_sqr)) * (point - _origin);
4588 else if constexpr(dim_ == 3)
4589 grad = (DataType(1) / Math::pow(norm_sqr, DataType(1.5))) * (_origin - point);
4590
4591 return grad;
4592 }
4593
4594 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
4595 {
4596 const DataType norm_sqr = (point - _origin).norm_euclid_sqr();
4597 if(norm_sqr < _eps)
4598 return HessianType::null();
4599
4600 HessianType hess(DataType(0));
4601 if constexpr(dim_ == 1)
4602 {
4603 // 1D hessian is null
4604 }
4605 else if constexpr(dim_ == 2)
4606 {
4607 const DataType denom = DataType(1) / (_ln2 * Math::sqr(norm_sqr));
4608 hess[0][0] = denom * (Math::sqr(point[0] - _origin[0]) - Math::sqr(point[1] - _origin[1]));
4609 hess[1][1] = denom * (Math::sqr(point[1] - _origin[1]) - Math::sqr(point[0] - _origin[0]));
4610 hess[0][1] = hess[1][0] = denom * DataType(2) * (point[0] - _origin[0]) * (point[1] - _origin[1]);
4611 }
4612 else if constexpr(dim_ == 3)
4613 {
4614 const DataType denom = DataType(1) / Math::pow(norm_sqr, DataType(2.5));
4615 for(int i(0); i < dim_; ++i)
4616 {
4617 for(int j(0); j < dim_; ++j)
4618 {
4619 if(i == j)
4620 {
4621 for(int k(0); k < dim_; ++k)
4622 hess[i][j] += DataType(k == i ? 2 : -1) * Math::sqr(point[k] - _origin[k]) * denom;
4623 }
4624 else
4625 {
4626 hess[i][j] = DataType(3) * (point[i] - _origin[i]) * (point[j] - _origin[j]) * denom;
4627 }
4628 }
4629 }
4630 }
4631 return hess;
4632 }
4633 }; // class HarmonicShellFunction::Evaluator<...>
4634
4635 public:
4637 PointType _origin;
4638
4639 public:

4642 {
4643 _origin.format();
4644 }
4645
4647 explicit HarmonicShellFunction(const PointType& origin) :
4648 _origin(origin)
4649 {
4650 }
4651
4653 void set_point(const PointType& origin)
4654 {
4655 _origin = origin;
4656 }
